Class Property

java.lang.Object
iscte.se.landmanagement.Property
public class Property extends Object
Represents a property with geographic and ownership details. Each property includes attributes such as area, perimeter, corners (coordinates), ownership information, and neighboring properties.

  • Constructor Details

    • Property

      public Property(int propertyID, double parcelID, double parcelNum, double shapeLength, double shapeArea, ArrayList<Coordinates> corners, int ownerID, String parish, String municipality, String island)
      Constructs a Property with full details including coordinates and neighbors.
      Parameters:
      propertyID - The unique identifier for the property.
      parcelID - The parcel ID associated with the property.
      parcelNum - The parcel number within its region.
      shapeLength - The perimeter of the property in appropriate units.
      shapeArea - The area of the property in appropriate units.
      corners - A list of Coordinates representing the property's boundaries.
      ownerID - The unique identifier of the property's owner.
      parish - The parish where the property is located.
      municipality - The municipality where the property is located.
      island - The island where the property is located.

    • Property

      public Property(int ownerID, double areaSum)
      Constructs a simplified Property for an owner with aggregated area information. Primarily used for summarizing properties owned by the same owner.
      Parameters:
      ownerID - The unique identifier of the owner.
      areaSum - The total area of properties owned by the owner.
